# InferTest — expected entailments
# Construct : DataPropertyAssertion over a multi-level subproperty hierarchy
#
# Alice's age is only asserted via hasExactAgeInYears. A conformant
# reasoner must also expose that same literal value through EVERY broader
# datatype property in the chain (hasAge, hasNumericAttribute,
# hasAttribute) — not just the one directly asserted. Missing any one of
# these means the reasoner (or your pipeline's materialisation step) isn't
# walking the full subproperty hierarchy for datatype properties.

@prefix : <http://example.org/infertest#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

:DataPropertyAssertion_Alice :dataPropertyAssertionHasAge "42"^^xsd:integer .
:DataPropertyAssertion_Alice :dataPropertyAssertionHasNumericAttribute "42"^^xsd:integer .
:DataPropertyAssertion_Alice :dataPropertyAssertionHasAttribute "42"^^xsd:integer .
